<h4><span>Uncle Nicolini</span></h4>
<p>T Rutherford has had a very strong premiere as a new author. I highly recommend reading their work, which is available <a href="/t-rutherford-author-page">here.</a> Keep an eye on them heading into 2020!</p>
<p>Woedenaz has developed a tasteful collection of themes that use impressive CSS and design skills. They are viewable <a href="/woedenaz/offset/1">here.</a></p>
<p>And last but not least, here is my favorite art piece from last year:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-952/HighwayAsh.png" style="width:50%" alt="HighwayAsh.png" class="image" /></p>
<p>Made by Woedenaz for uraniumempire for the 2019 Art Exchange. It's a beautiful rendition of the album in Uranium's <a href="/scp-952">SCP-952</a>!</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>UraniumEmpire</span></h4>
<p>Tsercele started off with <a href="/scp-4581">SCP-4581</a> and hit the g-ddamn ground running! Keep an eye on their hit series, <a href="/the-eternal-mxtape">The Eternal MxTape</a>.</p>
<p>The best skip of the year, in my humble opinion, was <a href="/scp-4504">SCP-4504</a>. If you've got some time, give it a read!</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>TheMightyMcB</span></h4>
<p>kybard showed up out of the blue and just started kicking ass and taking names! Be sure to check him out at <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/kybard">his author page</a> and read all three of his skips, because they're excellent.</p>
<p>One of my favorite skips from 2019, and one that I find to be massively underrated, was <a href="/scp-3638">SCP-3638</a> &quot;You Can't Be Serious!&quot;, by 440 Hertz. It even has a really fun collaborative art page!</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>gee0765</span></h4>
<p>I recommend <a href="/scp-4338">SCP-4338</a>, <a href="/scp-3272">SCP-3272</a>, <a href="/scp-4368">SCP-4368</a>, and <a href="/scp-4357">SCP-4357</a>.</p>
<p>My favorite breakout author of the year was none other than T Rutherford!</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Vincent Van Gone</span></h4>
<p>My favorite SCP of the year was <a href="/scp-4390">SCP-4390</a>, and Tanhony really popped off this year!</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Croquembouche</span></h4>
<p>I highly recommend you check out the End of Death subseries, <a href="/the-existential-maw-of-despair-national-park">Lookout 281.</a></p>
<hr />
<h4><span>A Random Day</span></h4>
<p>MUCKSCAPE/MEGAGRID/MAYHEM series (<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/muckscape-megagrid-mayhem-hub">http://www.scp-wiki.net/muckscape-megagrid-mayhem-hub</a>); Maim The Sky, Slay the Sun series (<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/maim-the-sky-slay-the-sun-hub">http://www.scp-wiki.net/maim-the-sky-slay-the-sun-hub</a>) are my picks.</p>
<p>There was exactly one author i can remember who wrote good-ass shit last year and his name is pedantique.</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>MalyceGraves</span></h4>
<p><a href="/scp-4140">SCP-4140</a>, <a href="/breakneck">Breakneck</a>, <a href="/scp-4840">SCP-4840</a>, <a href="/scp-4372">SCP-4372</a> and the new author Hatcheye are my picks.</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Elogee FishTruck</span></h4>
<p>Some great content got made for the International Group of Interest competition! I'd recommend you all check out the <a href="/sky-sermon-hub">Sky Sermon series</a>, <a href="/non-prophet-organization-hub">A Non-Prophet Organization series</a>, and <a href="/scp-4775">SCP-4775</a> and <a href="/scp-4642">SCP-4642</a> for the Meat Circus GoI!</p>
<p>My pick for best new author is <a href="/oricat-author-page">OriCat</a>. Go read some of their tales, especially, their Daevite-centric ones.</p>
<hr />
<h4><span>Roget</span></h4>
<p><a href="/adoption-poster-darius">Mr. DARE</a> is the best thing produced on the SCP Wiki in 2019. Try to prove me wrong. You can’t. It’s wickedly funny and made Wilson’s go from a group I had a positive opinion of to a favorite.</p>
